page.title: 09ECOLOGY-2
page.content:
Water birds on the mainly lowland pools and streams include mallard, heron,coot,kingfisher and canada goose.Curlew nest towards Tysoe and hobby and kestral birds of pray are seen.Game birds include pheasant, partridge,woodcock and snipe.Large flocks of lapwing,rook,redwing,gulls and starling feed in the fields.Woods and hedges are home for yellow hammer, wren,robin,sparrow,blackbird and thrush.Jay,wood-pigeon,collared dove and woodpecker are seen.At night there are little,tawny and barn owls when foxes bark and horseshoe and pipistrelle bats fly.
Roadside verges are white with cowparsley also cowslips,knapweed, coltsfoot,fleabane and cranesbill. woodlands are covered with bluebells in spring.
